  <div id="fragment-1">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The "<a href="http://www.curvycorners.net">Curvy corners</a>" script was orgionally developed by Cameron Cooke, I (<a href="http://blue-anvil.com">Mike Jolley</a>) have since modified it for use in JQuery. The end result is a JQuery optimised file, much smaller in size, and working perfectly. Packed it is just 9kb in size!</p>
    <h3>History</h3>
    <ul>

    <li><strong>9th August 2008</strong> -  Few fixes and enhancements</li>
    <li><strong>18th July 2008</strong> -  Now works in IE6,7, safari, and all other modern browsers. Fixed centering bug.</li>
    <li><strong>19th May 2008</strong> -  No extra padding, safari fixed, larger filesize to reduce overhead and increase speed.</li>
      <li><strong>6th March 2008</strong> - Can now have different padding amounts for each side (top, left, right, bottom). Lots of fixes. Happy.</li>

      <li><strong>5th March 2008</strong> - Bottom bar fixed when applying background image tile. Also fixed padding bug (bottom).</li>
      <li><strong>21st November 2007</strong> - More Bugs fixed in IE7</li>
      <li><strong>29th September 2007</strong> - Bugs fixed in IE7, file size now 28kb uncompressed!</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Known Issues</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>You can only align tiled background images to the top; there is NO way to make it work when they are bottom aligned (at least 5 hours trying yielded no results!)</li>
      <li>CSS Transparentcy does not work in IE do to browser limitations; use a png background image instead</li>
      <li><strong>Fixed</strong> - <del>Transparent boxes mess up in IE7</del></li>

    </ul>
  </div>
